01:43.973 --> 01:46.976
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:01.469 --> 02:06.430
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

02:27.669 --> 02:30.454
[ALARM BLARES]

02:30.585 --> 02:32.021
-YOU TRIPPED
THE DAMN ALARM.

02:32.152 --> 02:33.631
-LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

02:33.762 --> 02:36.504
-[ALARM BLARES]

03:16.370 --> 03:21.375
-[POLICE SIRENS WAIL]

03:34.214 --> 03:36.390
-[HEAVY BREATHING]

04:13.775 --> 04:15.124
-[METAL DETECTOR WHINES]

04:34.665 --> 04:35.623
-MORNING, IAN.

04:36.232 --> 04:37.407
-MORNING.

04:37.973 --> 04:39.583
-WHAT? WHAT'S THE MATTER?
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING AT?

04:41.019 --> 04:45.415
-TRUTH, BEAUTY,
THE AMERICAN DREAM.

04:46.547 --> 04:48.200
AH. WOULD YOU LIKE
A SARDINE?

04:48.331 --> 04:49.767
-NO, THANK YOU.

04:49.898 --> 04:51.552
-MY MOTHER, SHE, UH,

04:51.682 --> 04:53.205
USED TO FEED THESE TO ME
EVERY MORNING

04:53.336 --> 04:54.685
FOR BREAKFAST NO LESS.

04:54.816 --> 04:56.818
SHE WONDERED WHY I
TURNED OUT THIS WAY.

04:57.471 --> 04:59.386
ALL I WANTED WAS A
BOWL OF WHEATIES, MA!

04:59.516 --> 05:01.170
-HEY, I READ YOUR
POEM LAST NIGHT.

05:01.866 --> 05:03.346
-YOU DIDN'T LIKE IT,
DID YOU? I CAN TELL.

05:03.477 --> 05:05.087
ONLY, YOU'RE TOO
NICE TO LET ME KNOW,

05:05.217 --> 05:06.697
SO YOU'RE GONNA TELL
ME IT WAS BRILLIANT.

05:07.437 --> 05:08.525
-IT WAS.

05:12.094 --> 05:14.401
-AND, UH, WHAT MAKES YOU THINK

05:14.531 --> 05:15.924
I CARE WHAT YOU THINK?

05:16.054 --> 05:17.186
WHAT WAS YOUR FAVORITE PART?

05:17.839 --> 05:19.101
THE LAST VERSE, RIGHT?

05:19.841 --> 05:22.800
"THE DAY WAS MOVING WESTWARD
LEAVING COLORS IN THE SKY.

05:23.323 --> 05:26.238
"THE EASTERN BLACK WAS CHASING
HOLDING COLORS THAT HAD DIED.

05:26.369 --> 05:27.675
"THE DAY WAS RACING QUICKLY,

05:27.805 --> 05:29.416
"BUT COULD NOT
OUTRUN THE NIGHT.

05:29.546 --> 05:32.157
AND I RODE ALONG THE SEASHORE
TO THE CAVERNS OF DELIGHT."

05:32.810 --> 05:34.334
-YOU'RE A VERY TALENTED WRITER.

05:34.943 --> 05:35.900
-THANKS TO YOU.

05:36.553 --> 05:38.163
-ME? WHAT HAVE I
GOT TO DO WITH IT?

05:38.294 --> 05:40.209
-YOU HAVE EVERYTHING
TO DO WITH IT.

05:40.340 --> 05:43.734
YOU'RE MY INSPIRATION.
YOU'RE MY IDEAL.

05:44.648 --> 05:45.954
YOU'RE MY MUSE.

05:46.084 --> 05:47.129
-OH, IAN.

05:47.259 --> 05:48.609
-NO, YOU REALLY ARE.

05:48.739 --> 05:50.001
EVERY TIME I LOOK
AT YOU, THE WORDS

05:50.132 --> 05:51.481
AND THE RHYMES, THE PASSION,

05:51.612 --> 05:53.701
IT JUST, IT FLOWS
FROM MY SOUL, SHAUNI.

05:54.571 --> 05:55.833
-I HAVE TO GET BACK TO WORK.

05:57.835 --> 05:58.706
-RIGHT.

06:00.272 --> 06:01.970
AND I'LL BE AT MY OFFICE.

07:03.335 --> 07:04.293
-BEGGS.

07:04.989 --> 07:07.252
-LITTLE BUDDY.
WHERE THE HELL HAVE YOU BEEN?

07:07.383 --> 07:08.776
-LET GO.

07:09.559 --> 07:10.604
-WHERE'S THE BOX?

07:11.343 --> 07:12.606
-IT'S BURIED UNDER THAT TOWER.

07:15.522 --> 07:17.175
THE PLACE WAS
CRAWLING WITH COPS.

07:17.306 --> 07:18.655
I HAD TO STASH IT SOMEWHERE.

07:19.743 --> 07:21.702
-I OUGHTA KILL YOU
RIGHT HERE AND NOW.

07:22.442 --> 07:24.705
WE'D BE IN MEXICO BY NOW
IF YOU HADN'T SCREWED UP.

07:24.835 --> 07:26.489
-JUST CONTROL YOURSELF,
BEGGS.

07:26.620 --> 07:28.273
NOBODY KNOWS IT'S THERE.

07:28.404 --> 07:29.666
ALL WE'VE GOT TO DO IS WAIT
FOR THE CROWDS TO LEAVE.

07:42.592 --> 07:43.941
-BE RIGHT BACK.

08:07.574 --> 08:10.925
-I LOST IT SOMEWHERE...
SOMEWHERE RIGHT ABOUT HERE.

08:11.055 --> 08:12.274
I THINK.

08:13.797 --> 08:14.711
-WE GOT PROBLEMS.

08:23.372 --> 08:24.373
-SO WHAT DO YOU THINK?

08:25.374 --> 08:26.897
GOD, I HOPE YOU CAN FIND IT.

08:27.028 --> 08:28.420
IT'S LIKE MY FAVORITE
NECKLACE.

08:28.551 --> 08:29.944
I'VE WORN IT EVERY DAY.

08:30.074 --> 08:31.511
-WELL, YOU'D BE NAKED
WITHOUT IT, RIGHT?

08:31.641 --> 08:33.251
-[METAL DETECTOR SQUEALS]
-YEAH.

08:33.381 --> 08:34.251
-HEY, HEY, HEY.

08:34.383 --> 08:36.211
WHAT IS THIS, HUH?

08:36.341 --> 08:37.734
WHAT IS THIS?

08:37.865 --> 08:39.866
LOOK AT THIS.
LOOK AT THIS.

08:41.825 --> 08:42.957
EUREKA!

08:43.087 --> 08:45.089
BACK...
BY POPULAR DEMAND.

08:45.220 --> 08:47.614
FOR YOU, MY LOVE.
-IAN, THANK YOU.

08:52.836 --> 08:53.750
-THANK YOU.

09:12.552 --> 09:13.857
-CLASS MEETS THE
DAY AFTER TOMORROW.

09:13.988 --> 09:15.729
HOBIE AND I WON'T
BE BACK UNTIL THEN.

09:15.859 --> 09:17.818
-MITCH, I CAN DO IT.
NO PROBLEM.

09:17.948 --> 09:19.863
-YOU'RE SURE?
-IT'S MY DAY OFF!

09:20.734 --> 09:22.910
-YOU SURE YOU KNOW HOW
TO TEACH WINDSURFING CLASS?

09:23.040 --> 09:24.607
-[SCOFFING]
IN MY SLEEP.

09:24.738 --> 09:27.001
HEY LISTEN, YOU'VE GOT
NOTHING TO WORRY ABOUT.

09:27.131 --> 09:28.655
NOTHING AT ALL.

09:28.785 --> 09:30.570
OKAY, NOW YOU GO ON AND
BE A LITTLE INDIAN GUIDE,

09:30.700 --> 09:32.441
AND I'LL TAKE CARE
OF EVERYTHING.

09:32.572 --> 09:34.617
-ALL RIGHT, BEN'S GOT
ALL THE INFORMATION

09:34.748 --> 09:35.923
WHERE THE CLASS MEETS.

09:36.053 --> 09:37.359
-WOULD YOU GET OUT
OF HERE ALREADY?

09:37.925 --> 09:38.752
-OKAY.

09:49.327 --> 09:50.111
-HEY, IAN.

09:50.241 --> 09:51.199
-HI.

09:51.852 --> 09:54.115
-SO, DID YOU HAVE
A PRODUCTIVE DAY?

09:54.245 --> 09:56.987
-WELL, I DIDN'T GET A
WHOLE LOT OF WRITING DONE,

09:57.118 --> 10:00.600
BUT I FOUND MYSELF
A CORKSCREW.

10:01.426 --> 10:04.952
I FOUND MYSELF A, WELL,
HALF A WATCH ANYWAY.

10:05.082 --> 10:07.171
-PRETTY.
-AND A $1.27 IN CHANGE.

10:07.694 --> 10:08.912
IN HERE.

10:09.043 --> 10:12.133
AND UM, WELL I--
I MADE THIS FOR YOU.

10:14.875 --> 10:16.659
-HEY, THAT'S NOT BAD.

10:18.269 --> 10:20.707
-ONE MAN'S TRASH IS
ANOTHER MAN'S TREASURE.

10:21.229 --> 10:23.231
-THAT'S VERY SWEET
OF YOU, IAN. THANK YOU.

10:23.797 --> 10:25.450
-YOU'RE WELCOME.
-WOW.

10:25.581 --> 10:28.584
[PEOPLE ARGUING]

10:29.977 --> 10:31.065
-OH BOY.

10:31.892 --> 10:32.980
-DUTY CALLS.

10:33.110 --> 10:34.416
-I'LL SEE YOU LATER.
-OKAY.

10:35.896 --> 10:37.419
-HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY!

10:38.986 --> 10:41.684
[MEN ARGUE]

10:42.946 --> 10:43.817
-UNTIL TOMORROW.

11:12.497 --> 11:18.068
[METAL DETECTOR SQUEALING]

12:26.484 --> 12:27.703
-WHERE IS IT?

12:27.834 --> 12:29.357
-IT'S HERE, SOMEWHERE.

12:29.879 --> 12:31.446
JUST KEEP DIGGING.

12:41.804 --> 12:44.328
-BROOKE, THAT STORM
OFF OF BAJA

12:44.459 --> 12:45.547
IS STILL MAKING SOME
NOISE, SO WE'RE GONNA

12:45.677 --> 12:47.070
HAVE TO MOVE THE TOWERS
BACK AGAIN

12:47.201 --> 12:48.680
ON ALL SOUTH-FACING BEACHES.

12:49.246 --> 12:50.726
-OKAY. I'LL SPREAD THE WORD.

12:51.640 --> 12:53.990
-THANKS.
YOU'RE BEAUTIFUL.

12:55.426 --> 12:57.298
-YOU SURE YOU GOT
THE RIGHT TOWER?

12:57.428 --> 12:59.082
MAYBE IT WASN'T NUMBER 12.

12:59.213 --> 13:01.781
-IT WAS NUMBER 12,
BEGGS, BELIEVE ME.

13:01.911 --> 13:03.347
IT'S NOT SOMETHING
THAT I'D FORGET.

13:03.478 --> 13:05.045
-WELL THEN, MAYBE YOU
NEVER BURIED THE JEWELS.

13:05.175 --> 13:06.786
MAYBE YOU RIPPED ME OFF.

13:07.438 --> 13:08.962
-THINK I'D BE THAT STUPID?

13:09.092 --> 13:10.659
TAKE IT EASY, BEGGS.

14:09.109 --> 14:10.806
-AH, SUCH SPLENDOR.

14:11.372 --> 14:12.547
FROM AN ADMIRER, I TAKE IT.

14:12.677 --> 14:15.376
-THERE'S NO CARD.
-SECRET ADMIRER.

14:16.029 --> 14:17.987
-THERE'S SO MANY HERE, I
CAN'T EVEN COUNT THEM ALL.

14:18.553 --> 14:21.686
-THERE'S, UM,
THERE'S 137 OF THEM.

14:23.297 --> 14:24.602
-YOU SENT THESE FLOWERS?

14:25.168 --> 14:26.996
-THAT'S ALL THE
FLOWER SHOP HAD LEFT.

14:28.868 --> 14:30.391
-WHAT'S THIS ALL ABOUT, IAN?

14:30.957 --> 14:34.961
-IT'S ABOUT LOVE AND ROMANCE
AND ELEGANCE, PERFECTION.

14:36.440 --> 14:38.529
AND THE SALE OF MY FIRST POEM!

14:39.269 --> 14:40.357
-YOU SOLD POEM?

14:40.488 --> 14:41.619
-YES!

14:42.925 --> 14:43.883
-THAT'S GREAT.

14:45.188 --> 14:46.973
CONGRATULATIONS.
-THANK YOU.

14:47.103 --> 14:48.626
I COULDN'T HAVE
DONE IT WITHOUT YOU.

14:50.846 --> 14:51.891
-SEE YA.

14:52.848 --> 14:54.284
-HEY, BEN.

14:54.415 --> 14:55.764
-HARVEY, WHAT'S ALL
THIS I'VE BEEN HEARING

14:55.895 --> 14:58.462
ABOUT YOU TEACHING
A CLASS FOR MITCH?

14:59.681 --> 15:01.204
-WELL, HE ASKED ME
TO DO HIM A FAVOR.

15:01.335 --> 15:02.640
WHAT COULD I SAY?

15:03.206 --> 15:04.338
-YOU COULD SAY
THAT YOU DON'T KNOW

15:04.468 --> 15:05.948
THE FIRST THING
ABOUT WINDSURFING.

15:06.818 --> 15:08.211
-WELL, I WOULDN'T GO THAT FAR.

15:08.342 --> 15:10.387
-HAVE YOU EVEN
BEEN UP ON A BOARD?

15:11.214 --> 15:12.215
-IT'S BEEN AWHILE.

15:13.956 --> 15:15.958
BUT I'M GOOD WITH KIDS.

15:16.089 --> 15:18.091
-OH, I'M SURE.

15:18.221 --> 15:20.745
ESPECIALLY WHEN THEY COME
FROM THE MAYFIELD SCHOOL
FOR GIRLS.

15:21.703 --> 15:23.748
-HEY, I'M DOING A
FAVOR FOR A FRIEND.

15:23.879 --> 15:24.924
-[CACKLING] YEAH.

15:33.715 --> 15:35.064
-HI, HEY.

15:35.717 --> 15:37.110
YOU GUYS LIKE POETRY?

15:37.240 --> 15:38.154
LISTEN TO THIS, HUH?

15:38.285 --> 15:39.590
THIS IS BEAUTIFUL.

15:39.721 --> 15:41.853
"THE SEA CAN TAKE
A MAN'S LAST BREATH

15:41.984 --> 15:43.420
AS WELL AS GUIDE HIM HOME."

15:43.551 --> 15:44.769
"I LOVE THE..."

15:44.900 --> 15:46.206
-WE HATE POETRY.

15:47.816 --> 15:49.557
-OH. WELL.

15:50.340 --> 15:51.863
-HOW MUCH YOU WANT
FOR THAT THING?

15:52.429 --> 15:54.344
-METAL DETECTOR?
IT'S NOT FOR SALE.

15:55.041 --> 15:56.042
-HERE'S 50.

15:57.957 --> 15:59.959
-WELL, THAT'S A VERY
GENEROUS OFFER...

16:00.089 --> 16:00.829
-PLUS, ANOTHER 50.

16:01.525 --> 16:03.440
-YOU JUST BOUGHT
YOURSELF A METAL DETECTOR.

16:09.620 --> 16:11.971
GOOD METAL DETECTOR,
AS A MATTER OF FACT.

16:33.514 --> 16:34.776
HEY, HEY.
-HEY.

16:34.906 --> 16:36.169
HALF DAY TODAY, HUH?
-SPLIT SHIFT.

16:36.299 --> 16:37.735
I'M GONNA FINISH
UP AT HEADQUARTERS.

16:37.866 --> 16:39.041
-AH, I WAS HOPING YOU
COULD READ MY NEW POEM.

16:39.172 --> 16:40.260
-YEAH, GREAT. HERE.

16:40.390 --> 16:41.783
-BUT I HAVEN'T
FINISHED IT YET.

16:41.913 --> 16:42.914
-OKAY, I'LL READ IT TOMORROW.

16:43.045 --> 16:43.915
-NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

16:44.655 --> 16:45.917
YOU SEE, IT'S A
VERY NOCTURNAL POEM.

16:46.048 --> 16:47.571
IT MUST BE READ AT NIGHT
FOR MAXIMUM EFFECT.

16:48.268 --> 16:50.400
SO WITH THAT IN MIND,

16:50.531 --> 16:52.620
I WAS HOPING
MAYBE WE COULD HAVE DINNER?

16:52.750 --> 16:54.883
UH, POSSIBLY GO DANCING?

16:56.493 --> 17:00.367
-UM, IAN I THINK YOU MIGHT HAVE
THE WRONG IDEA HERE.

17:00.497 --> 17:02.108
I'M INVOLVED WITH SOMEBODY.

17:02.630 --> 17:03.718
-SO BRING HIM ALONG.

17:04.458 --> 17:06.112
-I'M VERY INVOLVED
WITH SOMEBODY.

17:06.242 --> 17:07.635
WE LIVE TOGETHER

17:07.765 --> 17:09.419
AND WE'RE BOTH
VERY MUCH IN LOVE.

17:09.550 --> 17:11.595
-AH, BUT DOES HE
TAKE YOU DANCING?

17:11.726 --> 17:12.857
SEE, I LOVE TO DANCE.

17:12.988 --> 17:14.468
AND I KNOW YOU DO, TOO.

17:15.251 --> 17:16.773
-AND HOW DO YOU
KNOW I LOVE TO DANCE?

17:16.905 --> 17:18.515
-BECAUSE IT'S
WRITTEN ALL OVER YOU.

17:18.646 --> 17:20.256
I CAN SEE IT IN YOUR HAIR

17:20.909 --> 17:22.084
AND IN YOUR EYES.

17:22.954 --> 17:24.739
AND YOUR FINGERTIPS.

17:27.655 --> 17:30.179
-WHOA, DON'T TELL ME
EDDIE GOT YOU ALL THOSE.

17:31.137 --> 17:32.442
NOT ON A LIFEGUARD'S SALARY.

17:34.227 --> 17:35.228
-THEY'RE FROM A FRIEND.

17:39.710 --> 17:42.670
HEY, NEWMIE, DO ME A FAVOR AND
KEEP THEM UNTIL YOU CLOSE UP.

17:42.800 --> 17:43.714
I'LL PICK THEM UP TONIGHT.

17:44.672 --> 17:45.499
-ALL RIGHT.

18:03.647 --> 18:04.866
-HEY, GO AND FIGURE THEY'D MOVE

18:04.996 --> 18:06.346
THE TOWER IN THE
MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT.

18:06.911 --> 18:08.565
-WE'RE NEVER GONNA
FIND THOSE JEWELS.

18:08.696 --> 18:09.697
THEY'RE GONE.

18:09.827 --> 18:10.959
AND WHY ARE THEY GONE?

18:11.090 --> 18:12.352
BECAUSE YOU'RE
A WORTHLESS FOOL.

18:12.482 --> 18:13.614
-I DON'T HAVE TO
TAKE THIS CRAP FROM...

18:13.744 --> 18:14.702
-THE HELL YOU DON'T!

18:17.183 --> 18:18.619
-MAN: GUYS, KNOCK IT OFF, MAN!

18:20.360 --> 18:22.013
-HEY! BREAK IT UP!

18:25.147 --> 18:26.148
-MAN: HEY, CHILL.

18:29.151 --> 18:30.587
-HEY, GET OFF.

18:31.327 --> 18:32.285
HOLD IT.

18:43.296 --> 18:44.166
-HI, SHAUNI.

18:46.429 --> 18:48.039
-EDDIE, WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE?

18:48.170 --> 18:49.650
I THOUGHT YOU WERE GONNA
TX WITH SOMEBODY TONIGHT?

18:49.780 --> 18:50.955
-I TRIED TO CHANGE
AND NOBODY WANTS

18:51.086 --> 18:52.479
TO WORK THE GRAVEYARD SHIFT.

18:52.609 --> 18:53.741
WHAT CAN I SAY?

18:53.871 --> 18:55.482
I'M STUCK, YOU KNOW?

18:55.612 --> 18:57.527
ESPECIALLY WITH MITCH
BEING ON THIS CAMPING TRIP.

18:58.049 --> 18:59.399
-I KNOW. I'M NOT BLAMING YOU.

18:59.529 --> 19:00.443
I UNDERSTAND.

19:01.314 --> 19:02.750
I JUST MISS BEING WITH YOU.

19:02.880 --> 19:03.881
I MEAN, I FEEL LIKE
EVERY TIME I'M GETTING

19:04.012 --> 19:05.883
OFF WORK, YOU'RE COMING ON.

19:06.014 --> 19:08.059
I FEEL LIKE WE'RE TWO
SHIPS PASSING IN THE NIGHT.

19:08.190 --> 19:09.539
-I KNOW AND I'M SORRY.

19:09.670 --> 19:10.888
THINGS ARE GONNA BE
BETTER, I PROMISE,

19:11.019 --> 19:12.542
AS SOON AS MITCH GETS BACK.

19:15.502 --> 19:16.372
GOTTA GO.

19:17.591 --> 19:19.419
I'M SORRY.
I REALLY AM SORRY.

19:19.549 --> 19:21.203
I'LL SEE YOU AT HOME, OKAY?

19:21.334 --> 19:22.291
THINGS ARE GONNA CHANGE.

19:22.422 --> 19:23.292
TRUST ME.

19:34.303 --> 19:35.391
-[SIGHS]

19:57.848 --> 19:58.893
-WELCOME.

19:59.023 --> 20:00.547
-WELCOME TO WHAT?

20:00.677 --> 20:01.548
-TO WHAT?

20:08.381 --> 20:09.904
TO THE CAVERNS OF DELIGHT.

20:15.257 --> 20:16.737
-WHAT DID YOU DO TO YOURSELF?

20:17.520 --> 20:20.741
-I SHOWERED. I SHAVED.
I CUT MY HAIR,

20:20.871 --> 20:23.222
I PUT ON MY TUX.

20:23.874 --> 20:24.788
-WHY?

20:24.919 --> 20:25.746
-WHY?

20:27.138 --> 20:28.139
WHY?

20:41.283 --> 20:44.155
I UH, I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT FIND
ME IRRESISTIBLE.

20:45.331 --> 20:47.333
-I FIND YOU
A LITTLE BIT CRAZY.

20:47.463 --> 20:50.945
-AH, SOMEWHAT DERANGED,
BUT I'M NOT CRAZY.

20:51.772 --> 20:52.773
HERE.

20:53.556 --> 20:55.428
-WE'RE NOT ALLOWED TO
DRINK ON THE BEACH, IAN.

20:56.255 --> 20:58.082
-JUST A SIP.
THAT'S ALL I ASK.

21:04.828 --> 21:06.265
-IAN, LISTEN...

21:06.395 --> 21:10.660
-TO DAYS OF EASE AND
NIGHTS OF PLEASURE.

21:17.319 --> 21:23.412
[WALTZ PLAYING]

23:54.737 --> 23:56.086
-I CAN'T DO THIS, IAN.

23:56.783 --> 23:58.045
-NO, NO--
SHAUNI, WAIT!

24:05.618 --> 24:07.315
[CHEERING]

25:03.763 --> 25:06.069
-GARNER, I DON'T
THINK THIS GUY DROWNED.

25:06.200 --> 25:07.593
DID YOU SEE THE
MARKS ON HIS NECK?

25:07.723 --> 25:09.072
-IT LOOKS LIKE SOMEBODY
CHOKED HIM TO DEATH

25:09.203 --> 25:11.292
WITH THEIR BARE HANDS.

25:11.422 --> 25:12.511
-NEWMIE, ARE YOU
SURE THIS IS THE GUY
YOU SAW FIGHTING AT TOWER 12?

25:12.641 --> 25:14.034
-HE WAS GETTING
HIS BUTT KICKED.

25:14.164 --> 25:15.383
I HAD TO PULL THE
OTHER GUY OFF OF HIM.

25:16.036 --> 25:18.168
-NEWMIE, I NEED YOU TO GO
WITH ME TO MAKE A POSITIVE ID.

25:18.299 --> 25:20.780
IN THE MEANTIME, IF I WERE YOU
I'D BE CAREFUL OUT THERE.

25:33.793 --> 25:37.884
[LADIES TALKING]

25:38.014 --> 25:38.841
-LADIES.

25:38.972 --> 25:40.800
GOOD AFTERNOON, HI.

25:40.930 --> 25:42.584
UH, GATHER AROUND,
LISTEN UP.

25:42.715 --> 25:44.455
HI, UH, MY NAME IS HARVEY

25:44.586 --> 25:45.979
AND I'M GOING TO BE
INSTRUCTING YOU

25:46.109 --> 25:47.850
IN THE FINER POINTS
OF WIND SURFING TODAY.

25:47.981 --> 25:49.504
BUT FIRST WHAT
I'D LIKE YOU TO DO

25:49.635 --> 25:51.375
IS WRITE DOWN YOUR NAMES
AND TELEPHONE NUMBERS

25:51.506 --> 25:52.594
FOR ME IF YOU WOULD.

25:52.725 --> 25:53.813
-[LAUGHTER]
-YEAH, RIGHT.

25:54.422 --> 25:56.990
-UH, STRICTLY
FOR SAFETY REASONS.

25:58.774 --> 26:00.776
AND THEN WE'LL GET
TO THE GOOD STUFF.

26:02.735 --> 26:04.867
GUYS, THE THING
TO REMEMBER IS,

26:04.998 --> 26:07.783
AS WITH ANY SPORT,
THE TOUGHEST PART

26:07.914 --> 26:09.002
IS GETTING STARTED.

26:09.698 --> 26:11.308
BUT ONCE YOU GET
THE HANG OF IT,

26:11.439 --> 26:13.702
IT COMES SECOND NATURE.

26:15.878 --> 26:19.403
IT'S REAL EASY, YOU JUST
GOTTA KEEP YOUR BALANCE.

26:19.534 --> 26:20.709
-THIS IS PATHETIC.

26:21.405 --> 26:23.451
-I'M GONNA TELL THE DEAN NOT
TO USE THE LIFEGUARDS AGAIN.

26:23.582 --> 26:25.366
OH, THIS GUY
DOESN'T HAVE A CLUE.

26:25.496 --> 26:26.323
-WOMAN: THAT'S FOR SURE.

26:29.413 --> 26:30.676
-BUT IT'S A LOT OF FUN,

26:32.547 --> 26:33.548
ONCE YOU GET IT...

26:34.331 --> 26:35.202
ONCE...

26:35.985 --> 26:37.726
[LAUGHING]

26:38.640 --> 26:40.294
-OH, HE'S CUTE.

26:41.295 --> 26:43.166
-THIS IS RIDICULOUS.
LET'S GO, GIRLS.

26:43.297 --> 26:44.124
-LET'S GO.

26:44.254 --> 26:46.169
[LAUGHING]

26:47.562 --> 26:48.432
-GIRLS!

26:49.259 --> 26:50.652
I WAS, UH...

26:51.305 --> 26:53.742
I'M JUST SHOWING THE
WORST-CASE SCENARIO, YOU KNOW?

26:53.873 --> 26:56.092
I MEAN, I'M REALLY GOOD
AT THIS.

26:56.223 --> 26:57.790
-NO YOU'RE NOT, HARVEY.

26:58.442 --> 26:59.400
BUT I AM.

26:59.879 --> 27:00.967
OR WAS.

27:01.445 --> 27:03.839
NOW GIRLS, WOULD
YOU COME BACK HERE?

27:03.970 --> 27:05.406
I'D LIKE TO TALK TO
YOU JUST FOR A MINUTE.

27:05.536 --> 27:06.668
GIRLS!

27:09.671 --> 27:10.280
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

27:10.411 --> 27:11.934
I'M LIEUTENANT EDWARDS.

27:12.500 --> 27:13.675
NOW, IF YOU ALL
WOULD LIKE

27:13.806 --> 27:15.503
TO STICK AROUND HERE
THIS AFTERNOON,

27:15.634 --> 27:17.461
I'D LIKE VERY MUCH
TO SHOW YOU

27:17.592 --> 27:19.289
A COUPLE OF THINGS
ABOUT WINDSURFING.

27:20.595 --> 27:22.292
ON THE UP-AND-UP, OKAY?

27:22.423 --> 27:23.554
GOOD.

27:25.078 --> 27:29.430
[SOFT ROCK PLAYING]

28:00.026 --> 28:03.899
♪ NO LIFE'S WORTH LIVING ON YOUR OWN

28:06.119 --> 28:09.862
♪ YOU'RE BETTER OFF SAFE AT HOME

28:11.298 --> 28:13.822
♪ BUT WINGS WERE MADE TO FLY

28:13.953 --> 28:19.349
♪ WINGS WERE MADE TO FLY

28:24.137 --> 28:28.532
♪ SHE FOLLOWS AS HE LEADS THE WAY

28:30.099 --> 28:34.234
♪ AND BITES THE WORDS SHE WANTS TO SAY

28:34.974 --> 28:37.890
♪ CUZ THIS WINGS WERE MADE TO FLY ♪

28:38.629 --> 28:42.851
♪ WINGS WERE MADE TO FLY

28:48.074 --> 28:50.946
♪ SHE CAN'T BREAK FREE THE CAGE

28:51.077 --> 28:53.819
♪ SHE HIDES HER TEARS IN THE RAIN

28:53.949 --> 28:58.127
♪ AND DREAM OF BLUER SKIES

28:59.172 --> 29:02.218
♪ CUZ WINGS WERE MADE TO FLY

29:02.349 --> 29:08.181
♪ WINGS WERE MADE TO FLY

30:14.900 --> 30:16.815
-I UNDERSTAND IF YOU DON'T
WANT TO TALK TO ME AGAIN.

30:19.469 --> 30:20.688
I FEEL LIKE, UH--

30:22.603 --> 30:23.778
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I FEEL LIKE.

30:23.909 --> 30:25.258
I'VE NEVER
FELT THIS WAY BEFORE.

30:25.780 --> 30:26.912
I'M SORRY, SHAUNI.

30:27.390 --> 30:30.219
I HAD NO RIGHT TO IMPOSE
MY FANTASIES ON YOU.

30:30.350 --> 30:31.351
I CROSSED THE LINE.

30:32.308 --> 30:33.919
I'D HAVE DONE THE SAME
THING IF I WERE YOU.

30:34.702 --> 30:36.225
GET THE HELL AWAY
FROM THIS LUNATIC.

30:36.356 --> 30:37.748
HE'S OUT OF HIS MIND.

30:41.665 --> 30:43.058
LOOK, I JUST CAME
BACK HERE TO TELL YOU

30:43.189 --> 30:44.146
THAT I'M BACK IN MY MIND.

30:45.234 --> 30:47.802
AND I APOLOGIZE IF
I EMBARRASSED YOU

30:47.933 --> 30:49.499
OR CAUSED YOU ANY HURT.

31:15.264 --> 31:16.178
-COME HERE.

31:20.443 --> 31:22.097
LET'S PUT THIS
IN YOUR LAPEL.

31:29.061 --> 31:29.931
-THANKS.

31:31.977 --> 31:33.195
ARE YOU SURE
YOU DON'T FIND ME

31:33.326 --> 31:34.283
JUST A LITTLE BIT
IRRESISTIBLE?

31:35.328 --> 31:36.329
-I MISS THE STARVING POET.

31:36.807 --> 31:39.419
-YEAH, SO DO I.

31:41.856 --> 31:43.379
-SO, HOW'D YOU PAY
FOR ALL THIS ANYWAY?

31:43.945 --> 31:45.555
-AH, WHAT DOES IT MATTER?

31:46.121 --> 31:48.297
LIKE THE SONG SAYS,
"MONEY CAN'T BUY YOU LOVE".

31:49.646 --> 31:51.126
BUT IT WAS SURE WORTH A TRY.

31:54.825 --> 31:56.044
I'M GONNA MISS YOU,
SHAUNI.

31:57.698 --> 31:59.265
YOU'LL ALWAYS BE
MY INSPIRATION.

32:14.541 --> 32:15.411
-EW.

32:15.542 --> 32:16.847
-I KNOW, HE'S BIZARRE.

32:20.895 --> 32:21.809
-IAN?

32:24.812 --> 32:25.726
IS THAT YOU?

32:27.771 --> 32:28.947
-UNFORTUNATELY.

32:29.686 --> 32:31.123
-I ALMOST DIDN'T
RECOGNIZE YOU.

32:32.080 --> 32:34.126
UH, FOUND THIS IN THE TRASH.

32:35.257 --> 32:36.258
DON'T YOU WANT IT NO MORE?

32:37.999 --> 32:39.958
-NO, JOE, IT'S A
PART OF MY PAST NOW.

32:40.828 --> 32:42.351
WHY DON'T YOU KEEP IT?

32:42.482 --> 32:44.310
WHO KNOWS, MAYBE YOU'LL
FIND YOUR DREAMS WITH IT.

33:10.118 --> 33:11.728
-WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL
ME ABOUT THE ROSES?

33:11.859 --> 33:13.208
-FOR ONE THING, I
HAVEN'T SEEN YOU.

33:13.339 --> 33:14.601
-SHAUNI, COME ON.

33:14.731 --> 33:15.689
-LOOK, IF IT BOTHERS
YOU THAT MUCH,

33:15.819 --> 33:17.734
I'LL THROW THEM AWAY, OKAY?

33:17.865 --> 33:19.171
-I DON'T WANT YOU
TO THROW THEM AWAY.
I HAPPEN TO LIKE ROSES.

33:19.301 --> 33:20.781
I JUST WANT TO KNOW
WHO THEY'RE FROM.

33:21.390 --> 33:22.696
-HIS NAME IS IAN.

33:22.826 --> 33:24.002
HE'S A POET.

33:24.132 --> 33:25.351
-A POET?

33:25.481 --> 33:26.613
-HE WRITES ON THE BEACH.

33:26.743 --> 33:28.310
HE'S VERY GOOD.

33:28.441 --> 33:29.659
HE'S BEEN GIVING ME
HIS POEMS TO READ.

33:30.356 --> 33:32.140
-SOUNDS LIKE A
REAL SENSITIVE GUY.

33:32.271 --> 33:34.751
-LOOK, EDDIE, THERE IS NO
REASON TO FEEL THREATENED.

33:34.882 --> 33:37.015
-I'M NOT THREATENED.
-HE SOLD HIS FIRST POEM AND
HE GOT A LITTLE CARRIED AWAY.

33:37.145 --> 33:39.104
-I RAN A CHECK ON YOUR
MAN'S FINGERPRINTS.

33:39.234 --> 33:40.757
THEY TURNED UP ALL
OVER A MOTORCYCLE

33:40.888 --> 33:42.803
THAT WAS USED IN A
BURGLARY NIGHT BEFORE LAST.

33:42.933 --> 33:44.152
-YOU TALKING ABOUT
THAT JOB UP IN MALIBU?

33:45.414 --> 33:46.981
-WHAT WAS STOLEN?

33:47.547 --> 33:49.288
-HALF A MILLION DOLLARS
WORTH OF JEWELRY.

33:51.812 --> 33:53.031
-DO YOU KNOW WHAT
KIND OF JEWELRY IT WAS?

33:53.161 --> 33:54.989
I MEAN, DO YOU THINK
IT WOULD REGISTER

33:55.120 --> 33:56.338
IN A METAL DETECTOR?

33:56.469 --> 33:58.253
-IT WAS ALL KEPT IN
AN ANTIQUE SILVER BOX.

33:58.384 --> 33:59.994
I IMAGINE THAT WOULD
REGISTER, YEAH.

34:02.997 --> 34:07.828
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYS]

34:20.058 --> 34:24.888
♪ WHEN I CALL YOUR NAME

34:27.630 --> 34:31.895
♪ DO YOU HEAR ME SING

34:33.592 --> 34:38.815
♪ YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
WHO MAKES ME FEEL LIKE THIS ♪

34:40.860 --> 34:46.127
♪ GIVE YOU ANYTHING,
I PROMISE I WON'T MISS ♪

34:47.650 --> 34:51.219
♪ GIRL IT'S YOU

34:51.350 --> 34:54.527
♪ I WANT TO CALL MY OWN

34:54.657 --> 34:58.487
♪ AND IT'S TRUE

34:58.618 --> 35:02.056
♪ THIS LOVE IS SET IN STONE

35:02.187 --> 35:07.061
♪ CAUSE I CAN'T STOP HOLDING ON
TO THIS ROMANCE ♪

35:08.976 --> 35:14.112
♪ AND THE WAY YOU LAUGH,
IT PUTS ME IN A TRANCE ♪

35:15.417 --> 35:17.071
♪ GIVE ME A CHANCE

35:30.911 --> 35:35.220
♪ LAY BESIDE ME UNDERNEATH THE STARS

35:38.397 --> 35:42.705
♪ OPEN UP SO I CAN SEE YOUR SCARS

35:44.229 --> 35:48.015
♪ GIRL IT'S YOU

35:48.146 --> 35:51.279
♪ THAT I WANT TO CALL MY OWN

35:51.410 --> 35:54.891
♪ AND IT'S TRUE

35:55.022 --> 35:58.156
♪ THAT THIS LOVE IS SET IN STONE

35:58.286 --> 36:02.116
♪ GIRL IT'S YOU

36:02.247 --> 36:05.424
♪ HOW DO I GET YOU ALONE

36:05.554 --> 36:09.036
♪ AND IT'S TRUE

36:09.167 --> 36:12.474
♪ IT SINKS DOWN TO THE BONE

36:12.605 --> 36:15.956
♪ GIRL IT'S YOU

36:16.086 --> 36:19.568
♪ THAT I WANT TO CALL MY OWN

36:19.699 --> 36:23.398
♪ AND IT'S TRUE

36:23.529 --> 36:26.445
♪ THAT THIS LOVE IS SET IN STONE

36:46.378 --> 36:47.683
-HI.

36:48.510 --> 36:51.121
-OH GOD, IAN, YOU
SCARED ME HALF TO DEATH.

36:51.687 --> 36:52.819
-I'M SORRY.

36:52.949 --> 36:54.342
I THOUGHT IT MIGHT HAVE
BEEN WHOEVER DID THIS.

36:55.213 --> 36:57.215
-WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
THAT YOU FOUND THESE JEWELS?

36:57.345 --> 36:58.651
WHY DIDN'T YOU CALL THE COPS?

36:59.739 --> 37:02.220
-BECAUSE I STARTED
BELIEVING IN MY OWN DREAMS.

37:02.785 --> 37:04.091
AND I THINK YOU DID, TOO.

37:06.093 --> 37:07.877
LAST NIGHT I HAD THIS
FEELING DEEP DOWN,

37:08.008 --> 37:09.227
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE IT CAME FROM,

37:09.792 --> 37:10.880
BUT I KNOW YOU FELT IT.

37:11.968 --> 37:13.013
-I'M CALLING THE POLICE.

37:16.973 --> 37:18.236
YEAH, THIS IS SHAUNI MCCLAIN.

37:18.366 --> 37:19.933
I'D LIKE TO SPEAK
TO GARNER, PLEASE.

37:20.325 --> 37:21.413
WELL, DO YOU KNOW
WHERE THE JEWELS ARE?

37:21.543 --> 37:23.066
DO YOU HAVE THEM?
ARE THEY GONE?

37:23.197 --> 37:24.546
-I HAD A FEELING THEY
MIGHT BE COMING BACK,

37:24.677 --> 37:26.331
-SO I HID THEM.
-WHERE?

37:26.461 --> 37:27.767
-OUTSIDE.

37:27.897 --> 37:28.724
-GARNER, IT'S SHAUNI.

37:28.855 --> 37:29.725
I FOUND IAN.

37:41.737 --> 37:42.738
[BLOWING]

37:49.658 --> 37:51.181
-TAKES YOUR BREATH
AWAY, DOESN'T IT?

37:52.835 --> 37:54.446
NO HEROICS, PLEASE.

37:54.576 --> 37:55.751
JUST HAND OVER THE BOX.

38:03.150 --> 38:04.107
THANK YOU.

38:05.065 --> 38:07.067
NOW, GET INSIDE.

38:24.040 --> 38:27.305
[FAST-PACED MUSIC]

39:30.629 --> 39:31.673
[YELLS]

39:40.160 --> 39:40.987
-I'M OKAY, I'M OKAY.

39:41.117 --> 39:42.292
GO ON. GET THAT SON OF A--

39:59.919 --> 40:01.877
-WHOAAAAAA!

40:12.671 --> 40:13.498
[GRUNTING]

40:40.220 --> 40:41.221
-HEY.

40:41.787 --> 40:43.266
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

40:43.397 --> 40:44.093
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
SUPPOSED TO BE ON PATROL?

40:44.224 --> 40:45.660
-BEN RELIEVED ME.

40:45.791 --> 40:47.183
SAID IT LOOKED LIKE I
COULD USE A DAY OFF.

40:49.055 --> 40:49.925
WHATCHA GOT THERE?

40:51.274 --> 40:52.972
-IT'S JUST SOMETHING
SOMEBODY MADE FOR ME.

40:53.755 --> 40:54.669
-OH, I LIKE IT.

40:54.800 --> 40:55.757
IT'S COOL.

40:56.497 --> 40:57.367
-IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

40:57.498 --> 40:59.413
-UH-HUH, FROM IAN?

41:03.112 --> 41:04.810
IS THAT WHY YOU WENT
LOOKING FOR HIM?

41:05.767 --> 41:07.290
-I DIDN'T WANT HIM TO GET HURT.

41:09.467 --> 41:11.599
-SHAUNI, I KNOW GUYS
HIT ON YOU ALL THE TIME.

41:13.122 --> 41:14.559
AND I KNOW YOU KNOW
HOW TO DEAL WITH IT.

41:14.689 --> 41:16.517
BETTER THAN I DO,
AS A MATTER OF FACT.

41:19.694 --> 41:20.869
THIS ISN'T GOING
TO BOTHER ME AS

41:21.000 --> 41:22.131
LONG AS YOU CAN
LOOK ME IN THE EYE

41:22.262 --> 41:23.393
AND TELL ME YOU LOVE ME.

41:25.221 --> 41:27.267
YOU DO THAT, I'M FINE.

41:28.660 --> 41:30.183
-I LOVE YOU.

41:33.534 --> 41:35.493
[GIGGLES]

41:38.191 --> 41:40.846
-SO, WHAT DO YOU
WANT TO DO TONIGHT?

41:42.021 --> 41:42.935
HOW ABOUT A PLAY?

41:44.023 --> 41:44.893
HOW ABOUT A MOVIE?

41:45.807 --> 41:48.854
BETTER YET,
LET'S GO DANCING.

41:49.768 --> 41:52.335
NOW, WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU WERE OUT ON A DANCE FLOOR?

41:53.380 --> 41:54.947
-WHAT DO YOU SAY WE
JUST TURN IN EARLY?

41:56.470 --> 41:57.515
-I CAN LIVE WITH THAT.

42:02.476 --> 42:07.525
[END THEME PLAYS]
